@{u}PREFACE:@{uu}

        The  Unpacker and the Unpacker.library program is copyright Thomas
        Neumann  and Safe Hex International.  The unpacker is freeware and
        may  be  freely  distributed as long as no changes are made to the
        distribution archive.

        We  hope  a  lot of Amiga users will benifit from our work. If you
        have  any  suggestions concerning improvments or unknown crunchers
        @{b}please@{ub} let us hear about them!

        There  are  a  lot  of  different  programs  in the demo drawer the
        average user can use to unpack files with.
@endnode
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Desc "Unpacker.library Documentation"
@next Unique
@prev Preface

@{u}INTRODUCTION@{uu} 

                            . Do you want to use a very easy way to unpack
                              and decrunch all types of files and archives
                              included Lha, Lzx and even DMS!!

                            . Do you want a simple and effecient solution?

                            . Did you know that no files are safe anymore?

                            . Are  you  aware  of the many new trojans and
                              viruses  are  being  distributed  hidden  in
                              archives and packed files?


If  you  can  answer yes to these questions - please read on!  Furthermore
you  will  be  able  to  prevent  the  spreading of future vira and trojan
horses by using our unpacker.library and unpacker program. 
@endnode
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Unique "Unpacker.library Documentation"
@next Used
@prev Desc
         
@{u}THESE UNIQUE FEATURES DESERVE YOUR SPECIAL ATTENTION@{uu}


           - The SHI unpack.library is a professional high tech package to
             implement  in  any  program,  where you want to use an unpack
             feature.

           - This  library  knows  a lot of different crunchers, about 130
             different crunchers and versions and most remarkabel the Lha,
             Lzx, Lhz, Lharc, LhaSFX, PAK and the @{" DMS packers " LINK Dms} too.

           - You  can  implement  this library in your favourite utilities
             like SID, DirectoryOpus or what so ever you like. 

           - In  the  package you will find instructions for an easy setup
             to a already existing program.  If you are programmer you can
             implement the unpacker.library quite free in your own program
             if you like.
@endnode
